  • Method Details

    • updatePhotos

      public void updatePhotos(Integer antiquityId, List<org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartFile> photos) throws IOException
      Updates the photos associated with a specific antiquity.

      This method performs the following operations:

      • Deletes all existing photos associated with the specified antiquity ID.
      • Processes and saves the provided list of new photos to both the file system and the database.
      If a file is empty or an error occurs during processing, an IOException is thrown.

      Parameters:
      antiquityId - the ID of the antiquity whose photos are being updated
      photos - a list of MultipartFile objects representing the new photos to be associated with the antiquity
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs while processing or saving the files
      See Also:
      • PhotoAntiquityRepository.deleteByIdAntiquity(Integer)
      • MultipartFile

    • findByIdAntiquity

      public List<PhotoAntiquity> findByIdAntiquity(Integer id)
      Retrieves a list of photos associated with a specific antiquity.

      This method queries the database to fetch all photos linked to the antiquity identified by the provided ID. Each photo is represented as a PhotoAntiquity object.

      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the antiquity whose photos are to be retrieved
      Returns:
      a list of PhotoAntiquity objects representing the photos associated with the specified antiquity
      See Also:
      • PhotoAntiquity
      • PhotoAntiquityRepository.findByIdAntiquity(Integer)
